  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">We consider in this letter the quantum limits for measurements on macroscopic bodies, which are obtained in a novel way, employing the concept of decoherence coming from an analysis of the quantum mechanics of dissipative systems. Two cases are analysed, the free particle and the harmonic oscillator and for both systems, we compare our approach with previous treatments of such limits.</subfield>
